thread.title: Canadian Residential Real-Estate Activity Plunged in January

author: Paul Vieira
title: Canadian Residential Real-Estate Activity Plunged in January
text:
OTTAWAâ€”Canadian residential real estate activity plunged in January to their lowest in three years as the impact of tougher mortgage-financing rules kicked in. Three-quarters of all major local markets recorded a drop in sales.
National home prices also rose at a tepid pace, as softness in the Toronto market led to the slowest annual gain in over two years.
